# Shopu — Setup Guide (for complete beginners)

This folder is your real, working app: sellers can sign up, build a shop, add products,
and customers can buy with Paystack. Follow these steps in order.

## Step 1: Create your accounts (if you haven't already)
- Supabase: https://supabase.com → New Project → name it "shopu" → set a database password
- Paystack: https://dashboard.paystack.com/#/signup
- GitHub: https://github.com/signup
- Vercel: https://vercel.com/signup (sign up using your GitHub account — easiest option)

## Step 2: Set up your database
1. In Supabase, open your project
2. Click "SQL Editor" in the left sidebar
3. Click "New query"
4. Open `schema.sql` from this folder, copy everything, paste it in
5. Click "Run"
6. You should see "Success. No rows returned" — that means it worked

## Step 3: Get your keys
**Supabase keys:**
1. In Supabase, click the gear icon (Project Settings) → "API"
2. Copy the "Project URL"
3. Copy the "anon public" key

**Paystack key:**
1. In Paystack dashboard, click Settings → "API Keys & Webhooks"
2. Copy your "Public Key" — it starts with `pk_test_` (this is the TEST key, safe to use while building)

## Step 4: Paste your keys into the app
1. Open `config.js` in this folder
2. Replace the three placeholder values with the keys you copied
3. Save the file

## Step 5: Put this on GitHub
1. Go to https://github.com/new
2. Name the repository `shopu`
3. Don't check any boxes (no README, no .gitignore)
4. Click "Create repository"
5. On the next page, follow GitHub's instructions under "...or push an existing repository from the command line" — or simply drag-and-drop all the files from this folder into the GitHub page in your browser (GitHub supports uploading files directly through the website — look for "uploading an existing file" link on the new repo page)

## Step 6: Deploy on Vercel
1. Go to https://vercel.com/new
2. Import the `shopu` repository you just created
3. Leave all settings as default
4. Click "Deploy"
5. Wait about 1 minute — Vercel will give you a live URL like `shopu.vercel.app`

## Step 7: Test it
1. Open your live URL
2. Click "Start your shop free" or any pricing button
3. Sign up with your email
4. Check your email for a confirmation link from Supabase, click it
5. Log in, create your shop, add a product
6. Copy your shop link and open it in a new tab — you should see your storefront
7. Click "Buy now" on a product — use Paystack's test card to confirm payment works:
   - Card number: 4084 0840 8408 4081
   - Any future expiry date, any CVV, PIN: 0000, OTP: 123456

## When you're ready to take real money
- In Paystack, switch from Test Mode to Live Mode (top-left toggle in their dashboard)
- Get your **Live** public key and replace the test key in `config.js`
- Redeploy (Vercel auto-redeploys when you push changes to GitHub)
- You'll also need to complete Paystack's business verification to receive real payouts

## If something breaks
- Open your browser's developer console (F12 or right-click → Inspect → Console tab) to see the error message
- Most issues are: wrong keys pasted in `config.js`, or forgetting to run `schema.sql`
- Come back here and paste me the exact error — I'll help you fix it